t:
if I'll be able to forget her. I'm still shaken from her suicide.

I call her voicemail to hear her voice again.


“I thought, we're supposed to do it
                                         together,”
                                her voice growled.
c:
From beyond her grave she cries,
With blood welling in her hollow eyes,
To take revenge, she arise,
To make me suffer and agonize.
